info:
  program: remind-me-to
  args:
    - "--color"
    - never
    - "--help"
  env:
    GH_TOKEN: ""
    GITHUB_TOKEN: ""
    NO_COLOR: "1"
    RUST_LOG: "off"
---
success: true
exit_code: 0
----- stdout -----
A CLI tool that scans source files for REMIND-ME-TO comments and checks if their conditions have been met

Usage: remind-me-to [OPTIONS] [PATHS]... [COMMAND]

Commands:
  check  Scan files for REMIND-ME-TO comments and check their conditions
  help   Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Arguments:
  [PATHS]...
          Paths to scan (defaults to current directory)
          
          [default: .]

Options:
      --color <COLOR>
          When to use colors: auto (default, detect tty), always, never. Respects NO_COLOR env var
          
          [default: auto]
          [possible values: auto, always, never]

      --format <FORMAT>
          Output format
          
          [default: text]
          [possible values: text, json, llm]

      --ignore <IGNORE_PATTERNS>
          Additional ignore patterns

      --no-gitignore
          Don't respect .gitignore/.ignore files

      --dry-run
          Find and parse comments without checking external services

  -v, --verbose...
          Increase verbosity (-v debug, -vv trace, -vvv trace with targets)

  -q, --quiet
          Suppress all output, only set exit code

      --log-level <LOG_LEVEL>
          Log level: error, warn, info, debug, trace

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

  -V, --version
          Print version

Comment Examples:
  Add REMIND-ME-TO comments to your source files. The tool scans for these
  and checks whether their conditions have been met.

  Basic syntax:
    // REMIND-ME-TO: <description> [when <condition>]

  Any comment style works (// , # , /* */ , -- , etc.).

  GitHub operations:
    // REMIND-ME-TO: remove workaround when owner/repo#123 is merged
    // REMIND-ME-TO: clean up shim when owner/repo#45 is closed
    // REMIND-ME-TO: bump dependency when owner/repo >= 2.0.0 is tagged
    // REMIND-ME-TO: drop polyfill when owner/repo#78 is released
    // REMIND-ME-TO: delete migration when owner/repo@abc1234 is released
    // REMIND-ME-TO: remove feature flag when owner/repo/old-branch is deleted

  Issues:
    // REMIND-ME-TO: revisit this when owner/repo#99 is closed

  Date-based:
    // REMIND-ME-TO: remove beta banner after 2025-06-01

  Nixpkgs:
    // REMIND-ME-TO: switch to native package when nixpkgs/hello >= 3.0

  Multiple conditions:
    // REMIND-ME-TO: drop compat layer when owner/repo >= 3.0 is tagged, owner/repo#200 is merged

  Shorthand (inside a repo that has a GitHub remote):
    // REMIND-ME-TO: remove hack when #42 is merged

